Of the working population, some       
village residents follow trades and   
professions such as Rector of Parish  
Churches, artist, children's author,  
postmistress and general shopkeeper,  
farmers, foresters and woodmen,       
gamekeepers, agricultural workers,    
guest house proprietors, teachers,    
district nurse, agricultural          
contractor, agricultural engineers,   
policeman and smallholders.  Other    
residents are employed outside the    
village as plumbers; carpenters;      
electricians; construction engineers; 
builders; remover of tree stumps;     
teachers; merchant navy,army, and     
naval officers; chef; estimator;      
solicitors; publishers; nanny;        
chemist; stockbroker; accountant;     
insurance broker; motor engineer;     
newspaper editor; computer consultant;
book illustrator and secretarial staff
